  "text": "diverging with the system size, or a first order phase transition into a dynamically non-attractive \"ferromagnetic\" phase, see e.g. [35] . It is a general property of inference problems that at the correct value of the parameters θ the static spin glass phase never exists. Indeed, when the parameters θ are the actual ones from which the graph was generated, the system satisfies the so-called Nishimori condition, and a very general result is that there is no static spin glass phase on the Nishimori line [CITATION_1] 36] .",
